RequestPlayerEndTurnEvent
Request a PlayerEndTurnEvent from the player The player may send another view event if the related request was sent between this and a previous non-request event Notify the player about being able to end the turn This event is sent after every other request during the "on going" game state to signal that no other requests are coming
RequestPlayerPingEvent
Request a PlayerPingEvent from the player The response will be used to determine whether or not the player is still connected This event is not related to other request events and can always be replied to This event is handled by the VirtualView and therefore does not pass through the ModelEventProvider

ResponseInvalidEvent
Event sent when the player sends an invalid event (Bad client) This event is handled by the VirtualView and should never be triggered by a valid client, therefore it does not pass through the ResponseEventProvider
ResponseInvalidLoginEvent
Event sent when the player sends a login event with an existing username or an invalid age The message sent back should be a displayable message with accurate information about what went wrong This event is handled by the VirtualView.
ResponseInvalidParametersEvent
Event sent when the player sends an event with invalid parameters This event should be used when a player send an expected event but using non-expected parameters
ResponseInvalidPlayerEvent
Event sent when the player sends an event when no events (except for pings) where expected from the player
ResponseInvalidStateEvent
Event sent when the player sends an event that wasn't expected This event should be used when a player send a non-expected event for the state the player is in
